Class ItemTreeNode<TREETYPE>

  • java.lang.Object
    • treeview.GenericTreeNode<TREETYPE>
      • treeview.ItemTreeNode<TREETYPE>
  • Type Parameters:
    TREETYPE - The ItemTreeElement for the TreeView. It is replaced with the specific type during instantiation.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ITreeNode<TREETYPE>

    public class ItemTreeNode<TREETYPE>
extends GenericTreeNode<TREETYPE>
    Extends the GenericTreeNode class and provides an implementation specific for nodes that are leafs (e.g. nodes that have no children). Thus this class is used as a means to specify data entries in the tree

      • checkItem

        public <T> boolean checkItem(T item)
        This method checks the current node against an item. If the passed item matches the current node then true is returned. Otherwise false is returned. The passed item matches the node if it is the same item or if the valueproperty is equal to the passed item. The type of the item is determined during the method call and thus a typeparameter is used.
        Specified by:
        checkItem in interface ITreeNode<TREETYPE>
        Overrides:
        checkItem in class GenericTreeNode<TREETYPE>
        Type Parameters:
        T - The type of the passed item
        Parameters:
        item - The specific item that is checked
        Returns:
        true if the passed item is matching the current node, false otherwise
